fields.title: Sum of Two Numbers
fields.description: Given two non-negative integers separated by a space, return their sum. This problem tests basic arithmetic operations and input parsing skills.
fields.constraints: Both numbers will be between 0 and 1000.

fields.title: Reverse a String
fields.description: Given a string consisting of alphabets, return the reversed string. This problem tests your string manipulation skills.
fields.constraints: The string will contain only lowercase alphabets.

fields.title: Find Maximum Element
fields.description: Given a list of integers separated by spaces, return the maximum element in the list. This problem tests your ability to iterate over a collection and compare values.
fields.constraints: The list will contain between 1 and 100 integers, each between -1000 and 1000.

fields.title: Check Palindrome
fields.description: Given a string, determine whether it is a palindrome (reads the same backward as forward). This problem tests your string manipulation and logical reasoning.
fields.constraints: The string will be between 1 and 100 characters long and contain only alphanumeric characters.

fields.title: Fibonacci Sequence
fields.description: Given an integer n, return the nth Fibonacci number. The sequence starts with 0 and 1, and each subsequent number is the sum of the previous two numbers.
fields.constraints: n will be between 1 and 30.

fields.title: Binary Tree Maximum Path Sum
fields.description: Given the root of a binary tree, return the maximum path sum. A path is a collection of connected nodes in a tree, where no node is connected to more than two other nodes. The path may start and end at any node in the tree.
fields.constraints: The number of nodes in the tree is in the range [1, 3 * 10^4]. Node values are in the range [-1000, 1000].

fields.title: Regular Expression Matching
fields.description: Given an input string s and a pattern p, implement regular expression matching with support for '.' and '*'. '.' matches any single character. '*' matches zero or more of the preceding element. The matching should cover the entire input string (not partial).
fields.constraints: 1 <= s.length <= 20, 1 <= p.length <= 30, s contains only lowercase English letters, p contains only lowercase English letters, '.', and '*'.

fields.title: Median of Two Sorted Arrays
fields.description: Given two sorted arrays nums1 and nums2 of size m and n respectively, return the median of the two sorted arrays. The overall run time complexity should be O(log (m+n)).

fields.title: Longest Valid Parentheses
fields.description: Given a string containing just the characters '(' and ')', find the length of the longest valid (well-formed) parentheses substring.

fields.title: Trapping Rain Water
fields.description: Given n non-negative integers representing an elevation map where the width of each bar is 1, compute how much water it can trap after raining.
fields.constraints: n == height.length, 1 <= n <= 2 * 10^4, 0 <= height[i] <= 10^5

fields.title: Merge K Sorted Lists
fields.description: You are given an array of k linked-lists lists, each linked-list is sorted in ascending order. Merge all the linked-lists into one sorted linked-list and return it.
fields.constraints: k == lists.length, 0 <= k <= 10^4, 0 <= lists[i].length <= 500, -10^4 <= lists[i][j] <= 10^4

fields.title: N-Queens
fields.description: The n-queens puzzle is the problem of placing n queens on an n x n chessboard such that no two queens attack each other. Given an integer n, return all distinct solutions to the n-queens puzzle.

fields.title: Sudoku Solver
fields.description: Write a program to solve a Sudoku puzzle by filling the empty cells. A sudoku solution must satisfy all the following rules: 1) Each of the digits 1-9 must occur exactly once in each row. 2) Each of the digits 1-9 must occur exactly once in each column. 3) Each of the digits 1-9 must occur exactly once in each of the 9 3x3 sub-boxes of the grid.
fields.constraints: board.length == 9, board[i].length == 9, board[i][j] is a digit or '.'

fields.title: Word Search II
fields.description: Given an m x n board of characters and a list of strings words, return all words on the board. Each word must be constructed from letters of sequentially adjacent cells, where adjacent cells are horizontally or vertically neighboring. The same letter cell may not be used more than once in a word.
fields.constraints: m == board.length, n == board[i].length, 1 <= m, n <= 12, board[i][j] is a lowercase English letter, 1 <= words.length <= 3 * 10^4, 1 <= words[i].length <= 10, words[i] consists of lowercase English letters

fields.title: LRU Cache
fields.description: Design a data structure that follows the constraints of a Least Recently Used (LRU) cache. Implement the LRUCache class: LRUCache(int capacity) Initialize the LRU cache with positive size capacity. int get(int key) Return the value of the key if the key exists, otherwise return -1. void put(int key, int value) Update the value of the key if the key exists. Otherwise, add the key-value pair to the cache. If the number of keys exceeds the capacity from this operation, evict the least recently used key.
